cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the development of a novel algorithm for reconstructing intermediate depth maps and estimating scene flow simultaneously using a hybrid camera. This involves computer vision, graphics, robotics, multimedia, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graphics and robotics, which makes cs.GR (Computer Graphics) and cs.RO (Robotics) likely sub-categories. The use of auxiliary color images and the development of a novel algorithm suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
